TIC80 - External Editor To get a better experience to edit the sprites and maps while also editing the code in an external editor we can use require
How to require a file Sadly lua require does not work the way as expected in TIC-80. We need to add the package path.
package.path = package.path .. &#34;;/Users/youruser/Library/Application Support/com.nesbox.tic/TIC-80/?.lua&#34; require &#34;game&#34;

Tables in Pico8 The Concatenation Trick For beginners, I suggest you use concatenation to index 2D arrays. Create a new object in a 2D cell at (i,j) in a table called myArray with the following code:
myArray[i..&#34;,&#34;..j] = {} To iterate over all objects in the myArray you can use the pairs iterator. Caution: the objects are not ordered when using pairs!
for k,v in pairs(myArray) do -- v is the cell object -- k is a string in the form of &#34;i,j&#34; end If we want to access the objects in a particular order we should use nested for loops:
